message.name: QuoteStatusRequest
message.description: This message is used to request a quote status report message.

message.name: SubscribRequestAck
message.description: The acknowledgement of SubscribRequest message to indicate whether it is accepted.

message.name: SubscriptionOrRedemption

component.name: SettlPtysSubGrp
component.description: the settlement member's detail information, especial account information.

field.name: BeginSeqNo
field.description: Message sequence number of first message in range to be resent

field.name: BeginString
field.description: Identifies beginning of new message and protocol version. ALWAYS FIRST FIELD IN MESSAGE

field.name: BodyLength
field.description: Message length; in bytes; forward to the CheckSum field. ALWAYS SECOND FIELD IN MESSAGE.

field.name: CheckSum
field.description: Three byte; simple checksum ("Checksum Calculation" for description). ALWAYS LAST FIELD IN MESSAGE with the trailing ; as the end-of-message delimiter. Always defined as three characters. (Always unencrypted)

field.name: Currency
field.description: Identifies currency used for trading. Absence of this field is interpreted as the default for the security. The dafult is CNY

field.name: EndSeqNo
field.description: Message sequence number of last message in range to be resent

field.name: IOIQty
field.description: (e.g. number of shares) in numeric form or relative size

field.name: IOITransType
field.description: Indicative Transaction Type N-New; C-Cancelled; R-Replaced

field.name: LastQty
field.description: Traded Quantity (e.g. shares) bought/sold on this (last) fill

field.name: MsgSeqNum
field.description: Integer message sequence number used for session management

field.name: PossDupFlag
field.description: Possible Duplicate Flag Indicates possible retransmission of message with this sequence number

field.name: Price
field.description: Trading Price Rate Fixed Rate Clean Price Fund Price Security Lending rate Repo Rate

field.name: SecurityID
field.description: Instrument Code or Standard Product Code

field.name: SenderCompID
field.description: Sender Company Identifer Assigned value used to identify member bank sending message.

field.name: SenderSubID
field.description: Sender Sub-Identifer Assigned value used to identify specific message originator (desk, trader, etc.)

field.name: Symbol
field.description: Trade Product Name or Currency Pair Name

field.name: TargetCompID
field.description: Target Company Identifier Assigned value used to identify receiving member bank

field.name: TargetSubID
field.description: Target Company Sub-Identifier Assigned value used to identify specific individual or unit intended to receive message. "ADMIN" reserved for administrative messages not intended for a specific user.

field.name: Text
field.description: Remarks At the time of negotiation, trader has an option to enter some remark in the remark field in the quote entry window. Remarks can be of maximum 100 Chinese characters.

field.name: SettlType
field.description: Settlement Speed Valid Values: 0 - Regular 1 - Cash(TOD / T+0) 2 - Next Day(TOM / T+1) 3 - T+2 4 - T+3 5 - T+4 6 - Future 7 - When And If Issued 8 - Sellers Option 9 - T+5 ON, TODAY, TN, TOM, SPOT, 1D, SN, 1W, 2W, 3W, 1M, 2M, 3M , 4M, 5M, 6M, 9M, 1Y, 18M,BROKEN; 7D;2Y;3Y;4Y;5Y;6Y;7Y;8Y;9Y;10Y;11Y;12Y;13Y;14Y;15Y;16Y;17Y;18Y;19Y;20Y;21Y;22Y;23Y;24Y;25Y;26Y;27Y;28Y;29Y;30Y;40Y;50Y

field.name: SignatureLength
field.description: Number of bytes in signature field.

field.name: RawDataLength
field.description: Number of bytes in raw data field.

field.name: RawData
field.description: Unformatted raw data. can include bitmaps. word processor documents. etc.

field.name: PossResend
field.description: Message Possible Resend Flag Indicates that message may contain information that has been sent under another sequence number.

field.name: EncryptMethod
field.description: Method of encryption.; Valid values:; 0 - None or other; 1 - PKCS (proprietary); 2 - DES (ECB mode); 3 - PKCS or DES (proprietary); 4 - PGP or DES (defunct); 5 - PGP or DES-MD5 (see app note on FIX web site); 6 - PEM or DES-MD5 (see app note on FIX web site)

field.name: OrdRejReason
field.description: Code to identify reason for order rejection

field.name: MaxFloor
field.description: Maximum Display Quantity(maximum display unit amount

field.name: TestReqID
field.description: Test Request Identifier Identifier included in Test Request message to be returned in resulting Heartbeat

field.name: OnBehalfOfCompID
field.description: Message Originator Assigned value used to identify firm originating message if the message was delivered by a third party i.e. the third party member bank would be delivered in the SenderCompID field and the firm originating the message in this field.

field.name: OnBehalfOfSubID
field.description: Message Originator Company Sub Identifier Assigned value used to identify specific message originator (i.e. trader) if the message was delivered by a third party

field.name: OrigSendingTime
field.description: Original Message Transmission Time Original time of message transmission (GMT+8) when transmitting orders as the result of a resend request.

field.name: GapFillFlag
field.description: Message Gap Fill Flag Indicates that the Sequence Reset message is replacing administrative or application messages which will not be resent

field.name: DeliverToCompID
field.description: Message Target Company Identifier Assigned value used to identify the firm targeted to receive the message if the message is delivered by a third party i.e. the third party firm identifier would be delivered in the TargetCompID (56) field and the ultimate receiver firm ID in this field.

field.name: DeliverToSubID
field.description: Message Target Company Sub Identifier Assigned value used to identify specific message recipient (i.e. trader) if the message is delivered by a third party

field.name: NoMiscFees
field.description: Number of repeating groups of miscellaneous fees

field.name: ResetSeqNumFlag
field.description: Message Sequence Number Reset Flag Indicates that the both sides of the FIX session should reset sequence numbers

field.name: NoRelatedSym
field.description: Specifies the number of repeating symbols specified.

field.name: BidForwardPoints
field.description: Bid F/X forward points added to spot rate. May be a negative value.

field.name: OfferForwardPoints
field.description: Offer F/X forward points added to spot rate. May be a negative value.

field.name: MaxShow
field.description: Maximum quantity (e.g. number of shares) within an order to be shown to other customers

field.name: XmlDataLen
field.description: Length of the XmlData data block.

field.name: NoRoutingIDs
field.description: Number of repeating groups of RoutingID (27) and RoutingType (26) values.

field.name: RoutingID
field.description: Routing ID Assigned value used to identify a specific routing destination.

field.name: Spread
field.description: Spread Basis points relative to a benchmark.

field.name: BenchmarkCurveCurrency
field.description: Benchmark Currency Identifies currency used for benchmark curve.

field.name: CouponPaymentDate
field.description: Coupon Payment Date Date interest is to be paid. Used in identifying Corporate Bond issues.

field.name: IssueDate
field.description: Issue Date Date instrument was issued. For Fixed Income IOIs for new issues, specifies the issue date.

field.name: StipulationType
field.description: Stipulation Type Haircut -Conversion Proportion (s) (%) Yield - Yield/ 1st Leg Yield Yield2 - 2nd Leg Yield StopYield-STOPYIELD Discount-discount rate;StrikeYield - Strike Yield;StopStrikeYield-Stop Strike Yield

field.name: StipulationValue
field.description: Value of stipulation For Fixed Income.

field.name: UnderlyingIssueDate
field.description: Underlying Issue Date Date instrument was issued. For Fixed Income IOIs for new issues, specifies the issue date.

field.name: CreditRating
field.description: Credit Rating An evaluation of a company's ability to repay obligations or its likelihood of not defaulting.

field.name: UnderlyingCreditRating
field.description: Underlying Credit Rating An evaluation of a company's ability to repay obligations or its likelihood of not defaulting.

field.name: MDEntrySize
field.description: Quantity or volume represented by the Market Data Entry

field.name: NoQuoteEntries
field.description: The number of quote entries for a QuoteSet

field.name: NoQuoteSets
field.description: The number of quote entries for a QuoteSet

field.name: QuoteEntryID
field.description: Uniquely identifies the quote as part of a QuoteSet. Must be used if NoQuoteEntries is used

field.name: QuoteSetID
field.description: Unique id for the Quote Set.

field.name: UnderlyingSecurityIDSource
field.description: Underlying Security ID Source Required if SecurityID is specified.

field.name: UnderlyingCurrency
field.description: Underlying Currency Identifies currency used for trading. Absence of this field is interpreted as the default for the security. The dafult is CNY

field.name: TradSesReqID
field.description: Unique ID of a Trading Session Status message

field.name: MessageEncoding
field.description: Message Encoding Type of message encoding (non-ASCII (non-English) characters) used in a messages "Encoded" fields

field.name: EncodedTextLen
field.description: Encoded Text Length Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedText (355) field.

field.name: EncodedText
field.description: Encoded Text Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the Text (58) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the Text field.

field.name: LastMsgSeqNumProcessed
field.description: The last MsgSeqNum (34) value received by the FIX engine and processed by downstream application, such as trading engine or order routing system. Can be specified on every message sent. Useful for detecting a backlog with a counterparty.

field.name: RefTagID
field.description: Reference Tag Number The tag number of the FIX field being referenced

field.name: RefMsgType
field.description: Reference Message Type The MsgType (35) of the FIX message being referenced

field.name: SessionRejectReason
field.description: Session Reject Reason 0 = Invalid tag number 1 = Required tag missing 2 = Tag not defined for this message type 3 = Undefined Tag 4 = Tag specified without a value 5 = Value is incorrect (out of range) for this tag 6 = Incorrect data format for value 7 = Decryption problem 8 = Signature problem 9 = CompID problem 10 = SendingTime accuracy problem 11 = Invalid MsgType 12 = XML Validation error 13 = Tag appears more than once 14 = Tag specified out of required order 15 = Repeating group fields out of order 16 = Incorrect NumInGroup count for repeating group 17 = Non "data" value includes field delimiter (SOH character)

field.name: BusinessRejectRefID
field.description: The value of the business level 'ID' field on the message being referenced.

field.name: BusinessRejectReason
field.description: Code to identify reason for a Business Message Reject message.; Valid values:; 0 - Other; 1 - Unkown ID; 2 - Unknown Security; 3 - Unsupported Message Type; 4 - Application not available; 5 - Conditionally Required Field Missing; 6 - Not authorized; 7 - DeliverTo firm not available at this time; 8-Security in Shut Period

field.name: MaxMessageSize
field.description: Number of MsgTypes (35) in repeating group.

field.name: NetGrossInd
field.description: Code to represent whether value is net (inclusive of tax) or gross.

field.name: UnderlyingCouponRate
field.description: Underlying Coupon Rate For Fixed Income.

field.name: NoPartyIDs
field.description: Number of parties. If have GroupGrp, Parties will be defined in GroupGrp

field.name: TestMessageIndicator
field.description: Indicates whether or not this FIX Session is a 'test' vs. 'production' connection. Useful for preventing 'accidents'.; Valid values:; Y - True (Test); N - False (Production)

field.name: CountryOfIssue
field.description: ISO Country code of instrument issue (e.g. the country portion typically used in ISIN). Can be used in conjunction with non-ISIN SecurityID (48) (e.g. CUSIP for Municipal Bonds without ISIN) to provide uniqueness.

field.name: MaturityDate
field.description: Maturity Date Specifies date of maturity (a full date). Note that standardized derivatives which are typically only referenced by month and year (e.g. S&P futures).may use MaturityMonthYear and/or this field. When using MaturityMonthYear, it is recommended that markets and sell sides report the MaturityDate on all outbound messages as a means of data enrichment.

field.name: UnderlyingMaturityDate
field.description: Maturity Date Specifies date of maturity (a full date).

field.name: NoSides
field.description: Number of Side repeating group instances. ; Valid values:; 1 - one side; 2 - both sides

field.name: LegPrice
field.description: Price for leg of a multileg

field.name: TradeReportID
field.description: Unique identifier of trade capture report

field.name: NoHops
field.description: Number of HopCompID entries in repeating group.

field.name: HopCompID
field.description: Assigned value used to identify the third party firm which delivered a specific message either from the firm which originated the message or from another third party (if multiple 'hops' are performed). It is recommended that this value be the SenderCompID (49) of the third party.Applicable when messages are communicated or re-distributed via third parties which function as service bureaus or 'hubs'. Only applicable if OnBehalfOfCompID (115) is being used.

field.name: HopSendingTime
field.description: Time that HopCompID (628) sent the message. It is recommended that this value be the SendingTime (52) of the message sent by the third party.Applicable when messages are communicated/re-distributed via third parties which function as service bureaus or 'hubs'. Only applicable if OnBehalfOfCompID (115) is being used.

field.name: HopRefID
field.description: Reference identifier assigned by HopCompID (628) associated with the message sent. It is recommended that this value be the MsgSeqNum (34) of the message sent by the third party.;Applicable when messages are communicated/re-distributed via third parties which function as service bureaus or 'hubs'. Only applicable if OnBehalfOfCompID (115) is being used.
